review_data: Reviewed in the United States on March 12, 2021
name: Charlotte
title: Great drinkable yogurt
review: I really enjoy yogurt but am lactose intolerant. I was very happy to find this drinkable cashew milk non-dairy yogurt. Each bottle has 3-4 servings. Its a great pick-me-up mid-morning or mid-day. The flavor is good, just like high quality yogurt. It also comes in single serving bottles. It contains all the probiotics I look for in yogurt. Smaller cartons just like regular yogurt are also available. Of all the nondairy yogurts - almond milk, coconut milk, oat milk, etc, this cashew milk yogurt comes the closest in taste and texture to regular yogurt. Definitely recommended.

title: Excellent source of probiotics without dairy
review: I needed a good source of probiotics and also calcium that wasn't dairy and this is it. Calcium pills have too many unhealthy byproducts and I don't like dairy so I wasn't getting enough probiotics because I don't eat yogurt. This solves both those problems. It's drinkable, and plant based, with one billion of probiotics per serving. Also organic, which is a plus and different flavors to choose from. But the word is out and sometimes these are sold out. Recommended.
